    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** pacing the lineup as our primary anchor; his score of 81.476095 is fueled by a stellar 0.393 xwOBA and a favorable matchup against Andre Pallante. While **Yordan Alvarez** remains the clear ceiling play, our high-upside strategy centers on capitalizing on stolen base opportunities against slow-working pitchers. **Hyeseong Kim** (70.528050) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (65.415022) provide excellent value, with the optimizer specifically rewarding their 100% and 92% SB-efficiency ratings against Ryan Feltner and Freddy Peralta, respectively. We are also leaning heavily into the platoon advantage for **Colt Keith**, whose favorable spot against Bello yields a strong 69.640960, mitigating the risk inherent in a day where several of our hitters are facing sub-3.00 xERA arms.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the exclusion of **Caleb Durbin**, who fell just short of the cut with a 43.738839 rating. While **Caleb Durbin** remains an elite SB threat, the daunting prospect of facing Tarik Skubal (2.71 xERA) suppressed his scoring floor, making him a less efficient start than **Junior Caminero**, despite the latter\u2019s own difficult matchup against Paul Skenes. Risks remain across the board, particularly with the \"Lineup Pending\" status for many of our assets, including **Dillon Dingler** and **Gary Sanchez**; their scores are contingent on confirmed batting order placement. Managers should closely monitor the weather and official lineups, as any negative shifts for **Trea Turner** or **Kyle Schwarber**\u2014who are already battling the efficiency drain of facing a sub-3.00 xERA arm in Chris Sale\u2014could necessitate late-game adjustments to protect our daily game caps.",
